  "dataFlow": "A build request enters via POST /api/build (browser) or POST /api/webhook (GitHub/Linear push) or the autonomy poller (Linear API poll). The FastAPI server validates auth (HMAC session cookie), rate-limits, and calls create_session() which writes an initial BuildSession to the in-memory _sessions dict and atomically persists it to app/logs/sessions/{sid}.json. run_build() is scheduled as an asyncio background task. Phase 1 (clone): git clone --depth 1 of the target repo into app/workspaces/{sid}/. Phase 2 (plan): PITER intent classifier runs via Claude SDK on the brief, selecting an ADW workflow template and injecting relevant lessons from .harness/lessons.jsonl. Phase 3 (generate): Claude Agent SDK spawns a session with bypassPermissions, receives the structured prompt, writes code to the workspace, and commits. Phase 4 (evaluate): a second Claude SDK session grades the git diff on 4 dimensions; if score < threshold the generator retries up to max_retries times. Phase 5 (push): git push via a configured GitHub PAT; Linear issue transitioned to Done via GraphQL mutation. Throughout, session.output_lines is appended to, and the WebSocket /ws/build/{sid} handler polls this list every 150ms, streaming JSON events to the browser. The SSE endpoint /api/sessions/{sid}/logs does the same via Server-Sent Events with cursor tracking. On terminal state, supabase_log.py fires a fire-and-forget write to the gate_checks table. Scan data flows separately: cron.py triggers scanner.py which writes JSON to .harness/scan-results/{project}/{date}-{type}.json; pi_seo_monitor.py reads these, diffs against previous .harness/monitor-digests/, and routes critical findings through triage.py which calls the Linear GraphQL API to create tickets and optionally sends a Telegram message. Telegram inbound messages flow: Telegram → /webhook/telegram FastAPI route → supabase_log.mark_alert_acked() for /ack_alert commands. MCP data flows: Claude Desktop calls mcp/pi-ceo-server.js over stdio JSON-RPC; the server reads .harness/ files and calls the Linear REST API, returning structured tool results.",
